ivardefs.name: active
ivardefs.desc: Whether this body site is in active use.

ivardefs.name: description
ivardefs.desc: A summary, characterization or explanation of the body structure.

ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: Identifier for this instance of the anatomical structure.

ivardefs.name: image_
ivardefs.desc: Image or images used to identify a location.

ivardefs.name: location
ivardefs.desc: The anatomical location or region of the specimen, lesion, or body structure.

ivardefs.name: locationQualifier_
ivardefs.desc: Qualifier to refine the anatomical location.  These include qualifiers for laterality, relative location, directionality, number, and plane.

ivardefs.name: morphology
ivardefs.desc: The kind of structure being represented by the body structure at `BodyStructure.location`.  This can define both normal and abnormal morphologies.

ivardefs.name: patient
ivardefs.desc: The person to which the body site belongs.

properties.desc: Record details about an anatomical structure.  This resource may be used when a coded concept does not provide the necessary detail needed for the use case.
